article.description: JaShaun Smith registered 16 points and four blocks as Longwood edged past Presbyterian 58-55 on Thursday night in its regular-season finale.
article.headline: Smith scores 16 to lead Longwood past Presbyterian 58-55
article.linkText: Smith scores 16 to lead Longwood past Presbyterian 58-55
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- JaShaun Smith registered 16 points and four blocks as Longwood edged past Presbyterian 58-55 on Thursday night in its regular-season finale. Longwood (14-17, 9-9 Big South) has sole possession of fourth place, securing the program's most conference wins since joining the league in 2012-13. Shabooty Phillips had 10 points for Longwood, which earned its fourth straight victory. DeShaun Wade added six rebounds. Owen McCormack had 12 points and eight rebounds for the Blue Hose (9-21, 6-11), who have lost six straight games. Michael Isler added 11 points and six rebounds, and Chris Martin had 10 points. The Lancers leveled the season series against the Blue Hose. Presbyterian finishes out the regular season against Charleston Southern at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
